You_can_earn_Honey_Gold_loyalty_rewards_.message: You can earn Honey Gold loyalty rewards points based on the eligible items you purchase from participating third-party merchants. Certain items,product categories, and purchases are ineligible for Honey Gold. Generally, these exclusions are determined by the participating third-party merchant, and not by Honey. If there are no eligible items in your order, you will not earn any Honey Gold on that order. Generally, we won’t be able to confirm the amount of your order which is eligible for Honey Gold (and whether any of your items are ineligible), until after you complete your order and make your purchase. Specific Merchant Exclusions Please note,additional exclusions may apply in addition to those listed below.

You_can_earn_PayPal_Rewards_points_based.message:
You can earn PayPal Rewards points based on the eligible items you purchase from participating merchants. Certain items, product categories, and purchases are ineligible for PayPal Rewards points. If displaying a PayPal Rewards points percentage reward rate (for example, 2% cash back on eligible items), or percentage reward rate range (for example, 1 to 4% cash back on eligible items) for a particular participating merchant the relevant percentage for your order will be applied to the subtotal of eligible items purchased from the participating merchant (excluding tax or any additional fees, such as shipping), in order to determine the amount of PayPal Rewards points you may earn for that order. Generally, these exclusions are determined by the participating merchant, and not by PayPal. If there are no eligible items in your order, you will not earn PayPal Rewards points on that order.

If displaying a PayPal Rewards points percentage reward rate (for example, 2% cash back on eligible items), or percentage reward rate range (for example, 1 to 4% cash back on eligible items) for a particular participating merchant the relevant percentage for your order will be applied to the subtotal of eligible items purchased from the participating merchant (excluding tax or any additional fees, such as shipping), in order to determine the amount of PayPal Rewards points you may earn for that order.

Generally, we won’t be able to confirm the amount of your order which is eligible for PayPal Rewards points (and whether any of your items are ineligible), until after you complete your order and make your purchase.
